==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water thermometer
<hw>Wa"ter ther*mom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A
thermometer filled with water instead of mercury, for ascertaining the
precise temperature at which water attains its maximum density. This is
about 39⟦deg⟧ Fahr., or 4⟦deg⟧ Centigrade; and from that point down to
32⟦deg⟧ Fahr., or 0⟦deg⟧ Centigrade, or the freezing point, it
expands.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water thief</ent>⟦br⟧
